    "overview_number": 5,
    "overview_title": "A Simulating Conversation",
    "overview_subtitle": "Simulating Simple Experiments",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students learn the meaning of the term simulation, they use spinners, coins, a random number generator, and tools of their choice to simulate situations such as taking a multiple-choice test or predicting the percent of female rabbits born on a farm. Students display their simulation results in a table and as dot plots, and they interpret the results in the context of the situation."
  },
